## Getting Started

```bash
kova              # Interactive CLI — start a conversation
kova model        # Choose your LLM provider and model
kova tools        # Configure which tools are enabled
kova config set   # Set individual config values
Kova Gateway      # Start the messaging gateway (Telegram, Discord, etc.)
kova setup        # Run the full setup wizard (configures everything at once)
kova claw migrate # Migrate from OpenClaw (if coming from OpenClaw)
kova update       # Update to the latest version
kova doctor       # Diagnose any issues
```

📖 **[Full documentation →](https://github.com/chiragborse1/Kova-Agent/docs/)**

---

## CLI vs Messaging Quick Reference

kova has two entry points: start the terminal UI with `kova`, or run the gateway and talk to it from Telegram, Discord, Slack, WhatsApp, Signal, or Email. Once you're in a conversation, many slash commands are shared across both interfaces.

| Action                         | CLI                                           | Messaging platforms                                                              |
| ------------------------------ | --------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Start chatting                 | `kova`                                      | Run `Kova Gateway setup` + `Kova Gateway start`, then send the bot a message |
| Start fresh conversation       | `/new` or `/reset`                            | `/new` or `/reset`                                                               |
| Change model                   | `/model [provider:model]`                     | `/model [provider:model]`                                                        |
| Set a personality              | `/personality [name]`                         | `/personality [name]`                                                            |
| Retry or undo the last turn    | `/retry`, `/undo`                             | `/retry`, `/undo`                                                                |
| Compress context / check usage | `/compress`, `/usage`, `/insights [--days N]` | `/compress`, `/usage`, `/insights [days]`                                        |
| Browse skills                  | `/skills` or `/<skill-name>`                  | `/<skill-name>`                                                                  |
| Interrupt current work         | `Ctrl+C` or send a new message                | `/stop` or send a new message                                                    |
| Platform-specific status       | `/platforms`                                  | `/status`, `/sethome`                                                            |

For the full command lists, see the [CLI guide](https://github.com/chiragborse1/Kova-Agent/docs/user-guide/cli) and the [Messaging Gateway guide](https://github.com/chiragborse1/Kova-Agent/docs/user-guide/messaging).

